<Content>Beautiful Hotel The Aldon Kempinski in Berlin was just a beatiful property. Some restoration is still going on but it is minimal and as of May 2006, they were finishing up the last suites. You can request a room away from the construction. A very elegant and very expensive hotel but worth the visit. Located just a few steps from the Brandenburg Gate it is walking distance from several sites and parts of the city that visitors would want to see. The service was excellent and prompt. Meals were on the very expensive side but the tea service was not to be missed. There several upscale and modestly priced restuarants within wallking distance. The spa and pool located downstairs was very nice and they offer great spa services. Nice touch, the hotel provides an umbrella for each guest just remember to bring it back each day. Guset rooms were beatifully decorated with wonderfully appointed bathrooms. Huge closets and prompt room service. 
